Asia
-----
[2] Pakistan (Multan)
Date: 24 Sep 2014
Source: The Frontier Post, APP report [abridged, edited]
http://www.thefrontierpost.com/over-9000-measles-cases-in-flood-hit-areas/


Exactly 16 special teams of the Extended Programme for Immunization (EPI) have treated 9343 cases of measles in flood-hit areas of the district so far by covering 868 cases today [24 Sep 2014]. The total number of teams raised for flood-hit areas was 22, out of whom only 16 reported.

An official source of Health told this news agency on Thursday [25 Sep 2014] that as many as 21 Union Councils (UCs) had been affected by devastating floods in Multan district.

[Byline: Imran Baba]

