Europe
----
[3] Germany (Karlsruhe)
Date: 23 Sep 2014
Source: KA News [in German, machine trans. abridged, edited]
http://www.ka-news.de/nachrichten/baden-wuerttemberg/Aussenstelle-fuer-Fluechtlinge-wegen-Masern-geschlossen;art505234,1482842


A new Refugee Reception Centre in Karlsruhe has been closed after diagnosis of a case of measles virus infection just 10 days after its opening. The case was recognised 10-14 days after the initial admission of refugees.

A spokesperson for the District Health Department stated that the Reception Centre would only be reopened when no more measles cases were identified. All current admissions to the Refugee Centre would be vaccinated. The current situation is under review. Previously, a measles case had been identified in Karlsruhe, and the infection had not spread as result of prompt vaccination. The new Reception Centre in Greschbach Road will remain under surveillance, and comprehensive vaccination of residents will be completed.

Last weekend, a little more than 300 people arrived in Karlsruhe seeking asylum. While this figure is lower than the expected 500 refugees, it is still well above the average for the past month. Since 1 Sep 2014, more than 4800 people had already arrived in Karlsruhe, a total greater than for the whole of 2010.

